'''[[Pseudo-]]Dorotheos of Monemvasia''' ({{lang-el|Δωρόθεος Μονεμβασίας}}) is the name given to the unknown author (or compiler) of a Greek-language [[chronicle]] titled ''Historical Book'' (Βιβλίον Ιστορικόν), published at [[Venice]] in 1631. The work contains a history of the world from [[Genesis creation narrative|Creation]] until the early 17th century, and purports to have been written by a non-existent [[metropolitan bishop|metropolitan]] of [[Monemvasia]] named Dorotheos. The book became a popular source of historical knowledge during the period of [[Ottoman Greece|Ottoman rule]] in Greece.


